criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients will be admitted to ICU between 18 and 85 years of age who will undergo
             extracorporeal circulation during cardiac surgery and provided written informed
             consent will be enrolled as candidates of case group.

          -  Healthy volunteers will be enrolled as control group.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients had a fever before surgery, regardless of the etiological evidence of
             infection;

          -  had anti-infective treatment before surgery;

          -  had gastrointestinal surgery which left the digestive system dysfunctional;

          -  had a history of CPB in 6 month;

          -  reject or abandon ICU therapeutic intervention.
